Install npm and node.js:
https://nodejs.org/en

TS stanalone
install into project
$ npm i -g typescript
$ tsc -v
use compiler to get JS file
$ tsc index.ts
create config file (TS will automaticall read it each time you run tsc)
$ touch tsconfig.json
add to tsconfig.json:
{
  "compilerOption": {
    "target": "esnext", // target to the lates ES6
    "watch": true, // run tsc every time file saved
// watch might work in some cases in a run time only. watch use example: "$ sass --watch style.scss style.css"
    "lib": ["dom", "es2017"] allow to run tsc with older version of dom classes
  }
}

React.js and TS
create project with dependencies for TS
https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/react.html (TS docs)
$ npx create-react-app my-app --template typescript

Run
from project directory
$ npm start dev
